  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd, \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb5\u0ba9\u0baf\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vigil in Mannar to protest attack, arrests on empty face mask protesters",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "A sit-in protest has been held in front of the Mannar District Secretariat at 11.30 am on the 29th of Friday, condemning the attack on the empty-faced peace protester and the arrests.",
        "The protest was organized by the North-East Coordination Committee in Mannar.",
        "The protestors strongly condemned the government's attack on the peaceful protestors.",
        "They also requested the Sri Lankan government to stop attacking peaceful protesters, journalists and civil society activists.",
        "Representatives of women's organizations, directors and employees of Mesido, human rights activists, youth and young women participated in the protest.",
        "During this, the North-East Coordination Committee issued a statement.",
        "We, the war-affected North-Eastern Tamil people, human rights defenders belonging to the minority community, civil organizations, women's organizations unite and request the government to release all the detained protestors.",
        "The disempowered ordinary people of the island of Sri Lanka ended the dictatorial Rajapaksa regime through a democratic people's struggle (Aragalaya).",
        "We are proud to be the people of the island of Sri Lanka. We bow to the people's struggle that brought the Rajapaksas, the chauvinist protectors responsible for the destruction of Tamils \u200b\u200band war crimes, to their knees. The entire country was waiting for a democratic regime change.",
        "However, it is an opportunistic argument that those who came to power due to the change of power brought about by people's struggle turn against the same people and suppress the voice of those people.",
        "We fear that the violent anti-democratic actions of the current Sri Lankan government will lead the country back into a dark age.",
        "Therefore, we request the government of Sri Lanka to stop the violation of the fundamental rights granted to the people by the constitution and to ensure democracy and the rule of law, the statement issued by the North East Coordination Committee further stated."
      ],
